tring using `lxml.etree.tostring()` with unicode encoding. I need to handle the case where `request.get_json()` might return None to avoid an AttributeError. Let me check form data first, then safely attempt to extract from JSON if needed:\n\n```python\nfrom flask import Flask, request\nimport lxml.etree\n\napp = Flask(__name__)\n\n@app.post(\"/parse_xml\")\ndef parse_xml():\n    '''\n    Get the data from the request using 'xml_src'.\n    Parse it as XML from the string.\n    :return: The XML as a string.\n    '''\n    xml_src = request.form.get('xml_src')\n    if not xml_src:\n        json_data = request.get_json()\n        if json_data:\n            xml_src = json_data.get('xml_src')\n    \n    tree = lxml.etree.fromstring(xml_src.encode())\n    return lxml.etree.tostring(tree, encoding='unicode')\n```\n\nThis approach safely checks form data first, then only attempts to access the JSON dictionary if it actually exists, preventing errors when the request body isn't JSON. it as XML directly. Since `request.form.get()` returns a string, I can pass it to `fromstring` without encoding. Let me simplify the implementation to just grab the XML from form data and parse it directly, returning the formatted result.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4732,"cache_read_input_tokens":24095,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4732},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3cec91b1-3358-4164-8c4e-5e055d4b25e7","uuid":"978f7afb-693a-4d6e-85d1-24b54175eefa","request_id":"req_011CbdRKvy7VyeLK5txc1jET"}
